cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NA, cs.DS, cs.SY 

The paper discusses the use of operator splitting methods in computational sciences, statistics, learning, and vision areas, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), numerical analysis (cs.NA), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithmic framework for deep-architecture-based operator splitting for nonconvex optimization, which is a common topic in machine learning and computer vision research. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.NA, cs.DS, and cs.SY.
